WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:28.090 --> 00:00:30.699
Not a bad afterlife. if you ask me.

3
00:00:33.810 --> 00:00:35.516
You're doing great. honey.

4
00:00:52.073 --> 00:00:54.882
Ok. I know how we're gonna save Leo. but how are we gonna save Morris?

5
00:00:54.882 --> 00:00:57.993
I have no idea. That's why they call it "winging it."

6
00:00:58.194 --> 00:00:59.699
What are you two talking about?

7
00:00:59.699 --> 00:01:00.401
Nothing.

8
00:01:13.446 --> 00:01:15.252
What are you waiting for? Attack!

9
00:01:24.284 --> 00:01:25.086
Leo?

10
00:01:27.495 --> 00:01:29.100
Ohh. What are we gonna do?

11
00:01:29.401 --> 00:01:32.612
It's Piper. Her pain is back. Do something.

12
00:01:33.515 --> 00:01:35.623
Uh...kill him!

13
00:01:44.854 --> 00:01:46.259
Take the fall.

14
00:01:46.360 --> 00:01:47.363
What fall?

15
00:01:49.069 --> 00:01:50.072
Stay down.

16
00:01:57.799 --> 00:02:01.110
What is he doing here? What are we doing here?

17
00:02:01.311 --> 00:02:02.716
Piper. shh!

18
00:02:03.920 --> 00:02:06.228
Ow. Do something.

19
00:02:08.135 --> 00:02:12.650
We just wanted to apologize for sending you such a weak warrior.

20
00:02:12.751 --> 00:02:14.657
We can get rid of him for you.

21
00:02:14.757 --> 00:02:16.162
Get rid of him?

22
00:02:17.266 --> 00:02:21.681
Yeah. You know. like...send his spirit on to. uh...

23
00:02:21.982 --> 00:02:23.989
the hereafter...or something.

24
00:02:25.996 --> 00:02:27.000
Very well.

25
00:02:40.647 --> 00:02:42.353
You left me. didn't you?

26
00:02:44.861 --> 00:02:46.065
Potion. potion.

27
00:02:49.377 --> 00:02:50.481
We got to get out of here.

28
00:02:58.609 --> 00:02:59.813
It's clear!

29
00:03:03.124 --> 00:03:04.228
I'll open the portal.

30
00:03:07.539 --> 00:03:08.342
Phoebe...

31
00:03:09.647 --> 00:03:14.162
It's Piper. Her heart is breaking.

32
00:03:14.564 --> 00:03:15.366
Piper.

33
00:03:15.366 --> 00:03:17.172
Don't. Stay away from me.

34
00:03:17.273 --> 00:03:19.480
I promise I will explain everything when we get home.

35
00:03:19.480 --> 00:03:20.986
but right now. we need to go.

36
00:03:20.986 --> 00:03:24.598
Home? We don't have a home. You left us!

37
00:03:25.401 --> 00:03:27.006
Leo. talk to her!

38
00:03:28.311 --> 00:03:31.321
I didn't have a choice. I became an Elder.

39
00:03:31.321 --> 00:03:33.629
It's not something that I wanted. It's something that just happened.

40
00:03:33.730 --> 00:03:37.242
Yeah. See. I know all of this. Why didn't I remember it?

41
00:03:38.646 --> 00:03:42.359
Because...I used my powers so you wouldn't have to.

42
00:03:43.965 --> 00:03:47.878
But your anger almost destroyed a city. and then your pain almost destroyed you.

43
00:03:47.878 --> 00:03:50.989
I wanted to help you so you wouldn't have to deal with it all at once.

44
00:03:51.591 --> 00:03:53.698
So you took my feelings away?

45
00:03:53.799 --> 00:03:59.017
No. Never! I was gonna reverse the spell slowly so you could feel

46
00:03:59.117 --> 00:04:01.325
a little more every day. but then...

47
00:04:01.325 --> 00:04:04.736
...somebody did this to me. Somebody put me here so I couldn't.

48
00:04:07.947 --> 00:04:09.152
I'm sorry.

49
00:04:09.252 --> 00:04:13.366
Look. I don't want to rush you two. but we have to go.

50
00:04:14.269 --> 00:04:15.774
I have to second that.

51
00:04:28.819 --> 00:04:33.937
You bastard. How dare you do this to me? To our son?

52
00:04:34.338 --> 00:04:35.141
Phoebe?

53
00:04:35.141 --> 00:04:40.058
We had a life together. a family. and you destroyed it. You destroyed me!

54
00:04:40.560 --> 00:04:45.878
You left me alone to raise our son by myself. How could you do this?

55
00:04:46.480 --> 00:04:47.885
How could you do this!!

56
00:04:49.992 --> 00:04:51.096
How could you!!

57
00:05:12.269 --> 00:05:14.577
I don't feel Piper anymore.

58
00:05:16.484 --> 00:05:17.587
We have to go.

59
00:05:22.404 --> 00:05:23.708
Come on. Piper. we got to go.

60
00:05:24.009 --> 00:05:25.615
Go? Go where?

61
00:05:26.016 --> 00:05:26.919
Home. Hurry.

62
00:05:29.829 --> 00:05:31.636
We got to leave her. Come on!

63
00:06:10.434 --> 00:06:12.114
Be careful of Darryl's body.

64
00:06:12.274 --> 00:06:16.195
Thank you. Is he-- I mean. am I still alive?

65
00:06:16.755 --> 00:06:17.875
Barely.

66
00:06:18.195 --> 00:06:19.075
Barely?

67
00:06:19.155 --> 00:06:20.355
We got to go back and get Piper.

68
00:06:20.675 --> 00:06:22.755
How? By force? She won't come. She's withdrawn.

69
00:06:23.235 --> 00:06:24.436
Besides. we can't go back now.

70
00:06:24.756 --> 00:06:25.636
But we can't just leave her there.

71
00:06:25.956 --> 00:06:28.756
Leo. they're not gonna hurt her. They need her to get to us.

72
00:06:28.916 --> 00:06:31.076
Listen. about my body...

73
00:06:31.876 --> 00:06:33.957
Oh. I'm sorry. You can just step right back in.

74
00:06:34.277 --> 00:06:36.677
That's it? I mean. even though I'm solid?

75
00:06:36.677 --> 00:06:38.117
You're still a spirit. Trust me.

76
00:06:38.197 --> 00:06:41.397
We got to go and figure out what to do. Thanks again.

77
00:06:44.918 --> 00:06:45.958
Don't mention it.

78
00:07:13.161 --> 00:07:15.321
Great. That's just great.

79
00:07:35.483 --> 00:07:37.484
Jeez. it's about time. I was starting to get wor-

80
00:07:39.324 --> 00:07:40.204
- where's Piper?

81
00:07:40.204 --> 00:07:41.484
Son of a bitch.

82
00:07:42.124 --> 00:07:43.084
Why'd you do it?

83
00:07:43.164 --> 00:07:44.044
Do what?

84
00:07:46.925 --> 00:07:48.045
Leo. stop it!

85
00:07:57.006 --> 00:08:00.206
Leo. enough! This hostility is killing me.

86
00:08:00.286 --> 00:08:02.686
What is wrong with you? You've been playing gladiator too long?

87
00:08:05.007 --> 00:08:06.287
You didn't tell them. did you?

88
00:08:06.447 --> 00:08:07.487
Tell us what?

89
00:08:07.487 --> 00:08:09.487
That he was the last one to see me.

90
00:08:09.647 --> 00:08:12.287
Right afterwards. I was mysteriously trapped in Valhalla.

91
00:08:12.367 --> 00:08:14.368
Oh. so what? That makes me responsible?

92
00:08:14.368 --> 00:08:15.408
Is that what you're saying?

93
00:08:15.408 --> 00:08:16.848
Ok. why would Chris do that?

94
00:08:16.848 --> 00:08:18.528
Why else? To get rid of me.

95
00:08:18.528 --> 00:08:19.488
It doesn't make sense.

96
00:08:19.648 --> 00:08:22.849
Doesn't it? You manipulated things so I'd become an Elder.

97
00:08:23.009 --> 00:08:24.449
Forced me out of the house. didn't he?

98
00:08:24.529 --> 00:08:26.849
So you could save the world.

99
00:08:26.929 --> 00:08:29.809
All right. Leo. I know how upset you are and by "know."

100
00:08:29.809 --> 00:08:34.130
I mean I literally know. But you're way off base here.

101
00:08:34.210 --> 00:08:36.610
Chris has been the model Whitelighter since you've been gone.

102
00:08:36.610 --> 00:08:37.730
He's done nothing but good.

103
00:08:37.810 --> 00:08:40.851
He sent us after so many demons. If anything. he's been too good.

104
00:08:40.851 --> 00:08:42.851
He's the reason we were able to save you.

105
00:08:46.371 --> 00:08:47.251
You're welcome.

106
00:08:47.571 --> 00:08:48.851
Where'd you get the pendants?

107
00:08:48.931 --> 00:08:50.132
Leo!

108
00:08:51.332 --> 00:08:54.852
All right. All right. I'll let it go for now.

109
00:08:55.732 --> 00:08:57.732
So where's Wyatt? Can I see him?

110
00:08:57.732 --> 00:08:58.613
No. you can't.

111
00:08:58.693 --> 00:09:01.333
He's staying with Sheila until we can figure out how to rescue Piper.

112
00:09:01.333 --> 00:09:03.893
Which is gonna be hard because she doesn't want to be saved.

113
00:09:03.893 --> 00:09:07.574
Well. if we're gonna save her. it's gonna have to be as witches. not as Valkyries.

114
00:09:12.854 --> 00:09:13.814
Book of Shadows?

115
00:09:13.894 --> 00:09:14.854
You got it.

116
00:09:32.696 --> 00:09:33.496
Well?

117
00:09:33.496 --> 00:09:39.577
She's Valkyrie. But it's not pure. Deep inside I sense -

118
00:09:39.657 --> 00:09:40.617
Witch?

119
00:09:41.497 --> 00:09:41.977
Yes.

120
00:09:42.857 --> 00:09:46.778
I told you. She came with the other witches. She has to be one. too.

121
00:09:46.778 --> 00:09:49.178
But it's very faint. I could barely read it.

122
00:09:49.258 --> 00:09:52.218
Still. she helped them escape with the warrior. didn't she?

123
00:09:52.218 --> 00:09:53.899
Yes. but she didn't escape with them.

124
00:09:53.979 --> 00:09:55.259
Maybe they left her behind.

125
00:09:55.419 --> 00:09:56.219
Why would they do that?

126
00:09:56.219 --> 00:09:58.139
Because they would have been caught if they hadn't.

127
00:09:58.779 --> 00:10:03.260
Either way. she can be of value to us. She wouldn't be the first witch to convert.

128
00:10:03.660 --> 00:10:06.140
And if she has. then we've gained a powerful sister.

129
00:10:06.940 --> 00:10:12.781
But if it is just a spell and she's not truly one of us. then we'll use her to lead us to the other two.

130
00:10:13.661 --> 00:10:19.021
After all. we can't have anybody knowing where to find us and risking what we do. now. can we?

131
00:10:19.021 --> 00:10:22.542
What about the warriors who followed them? Aren't you concerned about them being exposed?

132
00:10:22.542 --> 00:10:25.182
They're well trained. They'll know how to avoid it.

133
00:10:26.302 --> 00:10:30.543
Besides. hopefully they'll find the witches and take care of the problem for us.

134
00:10:31.023 --> 00:10:32.943
What do you think about that?

135
00:10:35.103 --> 00:10:38.944
I think that if they dont. we will.

136
00:11:02.466 --> 00:11:05.026
I don't understand. Why don't we just storm the place and find her?

137
00:11:05.026 --> 00:11:06.307
It's not like we don't know where she is.

138
00:11:06.387 --> 00:11:08.947
Because they would be expecting it. that's why. It'd be suicide.

139
00:11:08.947 --> 00:11:10.307
We got you out safely. didn't we?

140
00:11:10.387 --> 00:11:11.427
But it cost us Piper.

141
00:11:11.427 --> 00:11:13.827
Ok. you guys. would you knock it off?

142
00:11:14.227 --> 00:11:17.428
I'm still reeling from Piper's emotions. I don't need this.

143
00:11:18.948 --> 00:11:19.908
Sorry.

144
00:11:21.908 --> 00:11:23.108
So how's it going?

145
00:11:23.428 --> 00:11:27.909
I am almost done. I don't mean to burden you with my emotions.

146
00:11:27.989 --> 00:11:30.869
but I don't quite see how reversing the memory spell is gonna help.

147
00:11:31.189 --> 00:11:35.190
Piper needs to believe she's a Valkyrie because it's too painful for her to be herself.

148
00:11:35.270 --> 00:11:38.710
Way too painful. Believe me. I almost passed out back there.

149
00:11:38.710 --> 00:11:41.590
Well. then believing she's a Valkyrie is the perfect option.

150
00:11:41.590 --> 00:11:43.671
To serve the greater good. they're always in control.

151
00:11:43.751 --> 00:11:45.751
And they don't have to deal with pain or loss.

152
00:11:45.911 --> 00:11:48.871
Well. that's why we have to make Piper believe she's Piper again.

153
00:11:48.951 --> 00:11:52.232
Because if we don't get her back mentally. it won't matter if we get her back physically.

154
00:11:52.232 --> 00:11:55.272
Ok. but Piper wasn't exactly back before the spell either.

155
00:11:55.432 --> 00:11:55.992
What do you mean?

156
00:11:56.072 --> 00:11:59.912
Well. that little magical whammy you performed on her kind of. um. backfired.

157
00:12:00.233 --> 00:12:04.233
Yeah. You see. after you left. Piper was really...

158
00:12:04.313 --> 00:12:10.074
...chipper. Yeah. incessantly. increasingly...annoyingly chipper.

159
00:12:10.554 --> 00:12:11.354
What she said.

160
00:12:11.754 --> 00:12:13.354
Well. it was supposed to make her feel less pain.

161
00:12:13.434 --> 00:12:18.555
I guess with me not around to pull it back a little bit she got happier and happier.

162
00:12:18.635 --> 00:12:21.755
Uh. no. Psychotically chipper.

163
00:12:24.075 --> 00:12:24.955
Way to go.

164
00:12:25.355 --> 00:12:26.635
Chris...

165
00:12:27.035 --> 00:12:27.996
What?

166
00:12:28.156 --> 00:12:32.076
I swear my new power is gonna drive me crazy.

167
00:12:32.156 --> 00:12:33.996
You'll get the handle of it. Just be patient.

168
00:12:34.876 --> 00:12:40.717
Are you sure? Because I remember Prue almost being destroyed that time that she was an empath.

169
00:12:41.197 --> 00:12:43.437
Well. she wasn't supposed to become one. You are.

170
00:12:43.517 --> 00:12:45.998
Maybe all this with Piper has made it happen a little sooner.

171
00:12:46.158 --> 00:12:48.638
But you can handle it. I know you can.

172
00:12:48.718 --> 00:12:50.798
I just wish I knew how to turn it on and off.

173
00:12:50.958 --> 00:12:55.359
I feel like I'm at the mercy of everyone else's feelings. And it sucks.

174
00:12:55.439 --> 00:12:58.639
Bright side? Maybe you can actually find out how Jason feels about you.

175
00:12:58.799 --> 00:13:00.639
Yeah. but what if it's not good news?

176
00:13:00.719 --> 00:13:02.799
Ha! Then you dump him before he dumps you.

177
00:13:03.119 --> 00:13:06.720
Uh. I think the spell's finished.

178
00:13:11.680 --> 00:13:12.480
Oh. great.

179
00:13:13.681 --> 00:13:14.481
You got a dog?

180
00:13:14.561 --> 00:13:15.841
No. I got a career.

181
00:13:16.241 --> 00:13:17.841
Sore subject. Don't ask.

182
00:13:18.561 --> 00:13:21.041
All right. I'm coming.

183
00:13:29.362 --> 00:13:31.203
Oh. my god. Darryl. what happened?

184
00:13:32.323 --> 00:13:34.643
I think I just got attacked by Attila the Hun.

185
00:13:44.004 --> 00:13:48.724
Freyja. I need to speak with you. In private.

186
00:13:49.765 --> 00:13:51.365
You can speak freely.

187
00:13:52.165 --> 00:13:55.685
The warriors who followed the witches -- they've killed civilians.

188
00:13:56.325 --> 00:13:57.205
What?

189
00:13:57.365 --> 00:13:58.326
Innocents?

190
00:13:58.726 --> 00:14:00.966
I don't know. But they turned off their locators.

191
00:14:01.286 --> 00:14:02.646
What does that mean?

192
00:14:02.806 --> 00:14:07.206
They're trained to do that when the final battle between good and evil begins.

193
00:14:07.286 --> 00:14:08.567
We have to stop them.

194
00:14:08.567 --> 00:14:11.287
But how can we? We have no way of finding them in the city.

195
00:14:11.847 --> 00:14:15.687
I'm from the city. I can help you find them.

196
00:14:30.505 --> 00:14:31.466
Feeling better?

197
00:14:31.466 --> 00:14:33.708
Yeah. Thanks. man. It's good to have you back.

198
00:14:34.428 --> 00:14:35.630
Thanks for helping me get back.

199
00:14:35.870 --> 00:14:36.991
Ah. don't mention it.

200
00:14:38.192 --> 00:14:39.473
Would you...

201
00:14:41.315 --> 00:14:43.557
How long after we left did the warriors show up?

202
00:14:43.797 --> 00:14:46.039
Not long. Maybe a couple of seconds.

203
00:14:46.599 --> 00:14:48.441
They must have followed us from Valhalla.

204
00:14:49.402 --> 00:14:51.804
Great. That means they're after us now.

205
00:14:52.204 --> 00:14:54.526
Except they didn't hang out long enough to ask me where to find you.

206
00:14:54.767 --> 00:14:58.050
Granted. I was looking through swollen eyes. but they just seemed lost and confused.

207
00:14:58.610 --> 00:14:59.811
So what? They just took off?

208
00:15:00.131 --> 00:15:01.412
Thank goodness they did because--

209
00:15:01.493 --> 00:15:05.016
We should have never put you in that situation. We should have come up with another way.

210
00:15:05.256 --> 00:15:07.098
Forget it. You know. it worked.

211
00:15:07.098 --> 00:15:11.101
Yeah. for you maybe. What about the next poor guy that runs into those warriors? They're trained killers.

212
00:15:13.343 --> 00:15:15.105
Yeah. but they only kill evil.

213
00:15:15.185 --> 00:15:15.905
He's not evil.

214
00:15:16.386 --> 00:15:18.788
Chris is right. Not everything is black and white in this world

215
00:15:18.948 --> 00:15:21.430
And warriors can't always tell the difference between good and evil.

216
00:15:21.510 --> 00:15:22.551
What do we do?

217
00:15:22.551 --> 00:15:23.752
We need to find them fast.

218
00:15:23.913 --> 00:15:25.994
That shouldn't be too hard. They're gonna stand out

219
00:15:26.155 --> 00:15:27.436
...even in San Francisco.

220
00:15:27.516 --> 00:15:31.119
Which is why we need to move fast. If they're exposed. so are the Valkyries.

221
00:15:31.199 --> 00:15:33.601
You're awfully forgiving. considering everything they put you through.

222
00:15:33.921 --> 00:15:38.886
They still have a noble purpose to perform. Keeping their secret is key to them fulfilling it.

223
00:15:39.126 --> 00:15:41.848
Besides. it's not the Valkyries' fault that I ended up there.

224
00:15:41.929 --> 00:15:43.610
Which brings us back to the warriors.

225
00:15:43.690 --> 00:15:45.372
And let's not forget about Piper.

226
00:15:45.932 --> 00:15:48.655
Maybe we should split up. You should go to the police station.

227
00:15:48.735 --> 00:15:50.336
They're gonna show up on the radar screen in a big way.

228
00:15:50.656 --> 00:15:52.818
You know what? Office is paging me anyway.

229
00:15:52.898 --> 00:15:55.541
Make sure you're the first cop on the scene. We might need you to buy us some time.

230
00:15:55.621 --> 00:15:57.542
Ok. You got it.

231
00:15:57.863 --> 00:16:00.505
Uh. maybe I should go to the newspaper and do the same thing.

232
00:16:00.665 --> 00:16:01.466
Good idea. Paige -

233
00:16:01.706 --> 00:16:04.829
I should take Oscar home before I get fired.

234
00:16:05.069 --> 00:16:06.110
You're kidding. right?

235
00:16:06.110 --> 00:16:08.832
No. I promised the temp agency I'd have him back in the morning and.

236
00:16:08.832 --> 00:16:10.274
huh. it's the morning.

237
00:16:11.395 --> 00:16:14.518
Before you say anything. you've been gone. some things have changed.

238
00:16:14.518 --> 00:16:17.961
and one of those things is that I'm determined now more than ever to have

239
00:16:17.961 --> 00:16:20.363
a life separate from being a witch.

240
00:16:20.443 --> 00:16:22.204
Fine. but now?

241
00:16:22.445 --> 00:16:25.567
Yeah. I've already done the reversal spell. Can't do it without Piper.

242
00:16:25.647 --> 00:16:27.329
and we don't know how to get her. so

243
00:16:27.409 --> 00:16:29.251
...I'm just an orb away if you need help.

244
00:16:31.092 --> 00:16:32.053
Paige --

245
00:16:32.053 --> 00:16:35.816
Let her go. It might seem silly to you. but it's important to her. I know.

246
00:16:36.457 --> 00:16:37.898
See? It helps to be an empath.

247
00:16:38.139 --> 00:16:43.023
No. it helps to be a sister. And while we're on that subject.

248
00:16:43.183 --> 00:16:45.745
we have to come up with another plan to get Piper out of Valhalla.

249
00:16:47.587 --> 00:16:48.548
She's right.

250
00:16:49.909 --> 00:16:50.710
Come on. let's go.

251
00:16:50.710 --> 00:16:51.350
But-

252
00:16:59.037 --> 00:17:00.318
Come on. Get in there.

253
00:17:00.318 --> 00:17:01.279
Easy.

254
00:17:01.279 --> 00:17:02.961
Who goes there?

255
00:17:04.482 --> 00:17:06.484
What's the matter. don't you recognize me?

256
00:17:07.525 --> 00:17:11.128
Leo. But we'd heard that the witches had broken you out.

257
00:17:11.208 --> 00:17:14.171
Disinformation. Enemy's favorite tactic. Don't fall for it again.

258
00:17:14.811 --> 00:17:17.934
Right. Sorry. It's just that everyone's a little on edge.

259
00:17:17.934 --> 00:17:19.936
especially since the alert's been sounded again.

260
00:17:20.336 --> 00:17:24.820
I know. I found the intruder. Where's Freyja? She'll want to question him.

261
00:17:24.820 --> 00:17:26.902
She's not here. She went after the warriors in the city.

262
00:17:26.902 --> 00:17:28.423
And the new Valkyrie? Where is she?

263
00:17:28.744 --> 00:17:29.704
They took her with them.

264
00:17:30.505 --> 00:17:32.747
All right. Then I'll have to question him myself.

265
00:17:37.071 --> 00:17:37.872
Alone.

266
00:17:46.760 --> 00:17:50.683
What are you doing? Leo. what's going on?

267
00:17:51.484 --> 00:17:53.806
I'm gonna get the truth out of you one way or another.

268
00:17:55.808 --> 00:18:01.893
No sisters around here to help you this time. No orbing...no way out.

269
00:18:03.494 --> 00:18:06.697
Just you and me.

270
00:18:09.420 --> 00:18:10.541
You're joking. right?

271
00:18:10.541 --> 00:18:13.744
I mean. shouldn't we be getting back to filling in Phoebe and Paige and find Piper?

272
00:18:14.144 --> 00:18:15.825
I already lost Piper. Pick it up.

273
00:18:17.107 --> 00:18:20.630
You know. this isn't funny anymore. This isn't very Elder- like either.

274
00:18:20.710 --> 00:18:26.955
Yeah. being trapped here for five weeks and fighting for my life has changed me a lot. Pick it up.

275
00:18:27.916 --> 00:18:28.717
Forget it.

276
00:18:35.683 --> 00:18:37.044
I didn't do it.

277
00:18:42.409 --> 00:18:44.171
You can't kill me. I'm a Whitelighter.

278
00:18:44.651 --> 00:18:49.936
No? Then why are you sweating? ...I'm gonna find out the truth.

279
00:18:50.416 --> 00:18:52.898
I'm gonna find out who did this to me. I promise.

280
00:18:53.299 --> 00:18:57.222
Right now we're gonna go catch up with Phoebe and Paige and have a little chat with the Elders.

281
00:19:29.011 --> 00:19:32.053
This is the last place they were before they turned off their locators.

282
00:19:32.934 --> 00:19:36.217
Why did they do this? This is not what we're training them for.

283
00:19:37.098 --> 00:19:41.261
Maybe they were confused by all the evil in the city. It's everywhere.

284
00:19:41.502 --> 00:19:43.824
Then how will we find them before they hurt anybody else?

285
00:19:44.624 --> 00:19:46.146
I could scry for them.

286
00:19:46.146 --> 00:19:47.827
You mean like a witch can?

287
00:19:49.749 --> 00:19:50.790
What do you need?

288
00:19:50.790 --> 00:19:53.112
Something of the warriors'. The knife.

289
00:20:00.719 --> 00:20:01.279
Anything else?

290
00:20:02.480 --> 00:20:03.201
Well!

291
00:20:04.482 --> 00:20:07.925
Hell's bells. What have we got here? Ha ha ha ha!

292
00:20:08.726 --> 00:20:11.048
What. is there a Xena convention in town or something?

293
00:20:12.569 --> 00:20:13.610
On your knees.

294
00:20:14.331 --> 00:20:20.576
Excuse me? I got a better idea. How about you get on your knees instead?

295
00:20:25.221 --> 00:20:27.062
Who are you to speak to us that way?

296
00:20:27.062 --> 00:20:27.703
Kara.

297
00:20:27.863 --> 00:20:31.066
You don't command us. We command you!

298
00:20:35.550 --> 00:20:36.431
How dare you!

299
00:20:36.511 --> 00:20:39.553
This isn't Valhalla. You don't have dominion over men here.

300
00:20:41.235 --> 00:20:44.838
Then how do you train them? How do they take orders?

301
00:20:46.039 --> 00:20:48.361
They don't. They do what they want.

302
00:21:08.779 --> 00:21:11.742
You know. I have an idea of how we can blend in better.

303
00:21:55.861 --> 00:22:00.345
A motorcycle. Darryl? Are you sure? That is just so not Piper.

304
00:22:01.066 --> 00:22:04.829
Leo did say that she might be back. All right.

305
00:22:05.230 --> 00:22:06.831
Well. I'll call Paige. and you keep an eye--

306
00:22:07.552 --> 00:22:08.192
Oh. my god.

307
00:22:11.155 --> 00:22:12.196
Let me call you back. Let me call you back.

308
00:22:12.756 --> 00:22:15.639
Jason. hi. What are you doing here?

309
00:22:16.039 --> 00:22:17.721
Who. me? I own the place.

310
00:22:18.201 --> 00:22:21.324
Right. And I work here. That's why I'm here. Hmmm...

311
00:22:35.256 --> 00:22:37.658
Wh- what was I saying?

312
00:22:38.379 --> 00:22:39.660
Did you forget I was flying in today?

313
00:22:40.541 --> 00:22:44.945
No. Of course I didn't forget that you were flying back today.

314
00:22:45.986 --> 00:22:47.907
I'm just a little scattered. that's all.

315
00:22:48.628 --> 00:22:51.030
Is the air conditioning not working in here or what?

316
00:22:51.831 --> 00:22:58.477
Uh. it feels fine to me. Phoebe. you look great. Really. I like your hair.

317
00:22:59.838 --> 00:23:02.641
Thanks. I like yours. too.

318
00:23:03.762 --> 00:23:06.804
Uh. listen. I was gonna go home. unpack. take a shower.

319
00:23:07.044 --> 00:23:10.568
but I was hoping that maybe later we could get together and have some dinner.

320
00:23:10.808 --> 00:23:13.210
You know. I know we don't have anything planned officially.

321
00:23:13.370 --> 00:23:15.692
but I was thinking that because...

322
00:23:21.057 --> 00:23:22.658
I'm gonna take that as a "yes." then?

323
00:23:22.819 --> 00:23:23.940
Oh. no. no. no. no.

324
00:23:25.141 --> 00:23:25.861
No. no. no. no. No.

325
00:23:26.262 --> 00:23:33.788
No? All right. uh...I just really missed you. Phoebe.

326
00:23:34.029 --> 00:23:36.190
Oh. I know. I can tell.

327
00:23:36.751 --> 00:23:44.518
Uh...it's just. uh...it's very hard -- I mean. I mean...hard to explain.

328
00:23:44.758 --> 00:23:47.801
That kind of hard. you know. Not the other kind of hard.

329
00:23:48.121 --> 00:23:49.642
Am I making any sense?

330
00:23:50.123 --> 00:23:51.644
Phoebe.

331
00:23:51.724 --> 00:23:52.285
No. no. no. no.

332
00:23:52.525 --> 00:23:56.288
Don't come any closer. It'll just get harder. Phew.

333
00:23:58.290 --> 00:23:58.851
Oh. god.

334
00:23:59.811 --> 00:24:04.856
Oh. god. I ju...I ca...I ca- ca...I can't.

335
00:24:05.016 --> 00:24:06.938
Say bye- ye. Bye- bye. Bye- bye. B...

336
00:24:47.854 --> 00:24:49.696
No. wait. It's me.

337
00:24:50.817 --> 00:24:54.100
You're making a mistake. This is not the final battle.

338
00:24:54.260 --> 00:24:56.102
We've come to take you back to Valhalla.

339
00:24:58.023 --> 00:24:59.144
What do you think?

340
00:25:00.025 --> 00:25:01.706
I think the enemy wears many masks.

341
00:25:13.498 --> 00:25:16.465
Look. You're the agency. How could you not know they were leaving town?

342
00:25:16.786 --> 00:25:21.597
They abandoned their dog. That is animal cruelty. ok? No!

343
00:25:21.597 --> 00:25:26.088
I can't take care of the dog. I've got responsibilities. pressing ones. too.

344
00:25:26.168 --> 00:25:29.536
And besides. I need to make a statement to my family. This is not helping here.

345
00:25:31.139 --> 00:25:33.144
Hello? Hello?

346
00:25:37.154 --> 00:25:38.677
What am I doing?

347
00:25:40.201 --> 00:25:44.130
Ok. I'm just gonna have to trust the universe. Things happen for a reason.

348
00:25:48.139 --> 00:25:49.823
What is going on here?

349
00:25:50.064 --> 00:25:51.668
Bad- ass fight. that's what.

350
00:25:56.800 --> 00:25:57.762
Who said that?

351
00:25:58.003 --> 00:26:00.408
Whoa. Wait. You mean you can hear me?

352
00:26:01.210 --> 00:26:03.616
Well. hallelujah. It's about time.

353
00:26:04.498 --> 00:26:06.984
Please don't tell me you're talking to me.

354
00:26:07.144 --> 00:26:07.946
Are you kidding?

355
00:26:08.026 --> 00:26:10.272
I've been trying to get your attention for two days now.

356
00:26:10.272 --> 00:26:11.555
I'm in serious trouble. here.

357
00:26:11.875 --> 00:26:16.526
Ok. It's ok. Paige. You've dealt with weirder things than this.

358
00:26:16.767 --> 00:26:20.856
Hey. maybe- maybe my powers are just advancing. Maybe I can understand animals now.

359
00:26:21.097 --> 00:26:22.540
Oh. please. Give me a break.

360
00:26:23.102 --> 00:26:25.668
Until you accepted that there might be a reason you got this job.

361
00:26:25.908 --> 00:26:27.272
you weren't gonna be open to helping me.

362
00:26:28.314 --> 00:26:29.517
Help you do what?

363
00:26:29.918 --> 00:26:32.644
Reverse an evil witch's curse and make me human again.

364
00:26:33.606 --> 00:26:36.573
Come on. If I'm evil. too. it won't work. You know that.

365
00:26:38.498 --> 00:26:40.342
What have you got to lose?

366
00:26:40.984 --> 00:26:44.352
Well. that's a good point. This day couldn't get much suckier.

367
00:26:45.073 --> 00:26:48.121
Ok. here goes. Uh...

368
00:26:49.083 --> 00:26:50.927
I call upon the Halliwells.

369
00:26:51.088 --> 00:26:53.493
I call our powers to undo this spell.

370
00:26:53.573 --> 00:26:55.177
make right again. that we must.

371
00:26:55.338 --> 00:26:58.144
reverse the curse that made this mutt.

372
00:27:02.474 --> 00:27:04.639
Whew. That's better. Thanks.

373
00:27:07.045 --> 00:27:08.649
All right. don't mention it.

374
00:27:08.649 --> 00:27:10.814
As long as you don't hump my leg anymore. we'll be cool.

375
00:27:11.215 --> 00:27:14.663
Ahem. Yeah. Sorry. That's just what dogs do when they like someone.

376
00:27:15.705 --> 00:27:22.201
Aw. That's very sweet. Why did an evil witch turn you into man's best friend. anyway?

377
00:27:22.361 --> 00:27:25.970
Well. it's kind of complicated. Let's just say there were a million reasons.

378
00:27:26.290 --> 00:27:28.937
But let me help you. All those dogs out there.

379
00:27:29.097 --> 00:27:31.743
they're barking because there's some serious magic in the air.

380
00:27:31.904 --> 00:27:33.588
the kind of magic that you might be looking for.

381
00:27:39.842 --> 00:27:41.687
I am so sorry.

382
00:27:42.168 --> 00:27:43.771
I didn't mean for that to happen.

383
00:27:44.573 --> 00:27:48.583
Why not? Why are you apologizing? You were unbelievably--

384
00:27:48.583 --> 00:27:50.106
Oh. please don't say it. Just don't.

385
00:27:50.106 --> 00:27:52.512
Well. it wasn't just you. you know?

386
00:27:52.672 --> 00:27:58.927
Oh. yeah. I know. I just-- I. uh. I wasn't myself that's all.

387
00:27:59.809 --> 00:28:00.771
I don't understand.

388
00:28:01.012 --> 00:28:02.536
Yeah. I know you don't. and that's ok.

389
00:28:03.418 --> 00:28:07.187
As long as you stay on that side of the room. everything should be fine.

390
00:28:07.908 --> 00:28:09.913
It's the only way that I really know what I'm feeling.

391
00:28:10.635 --> 00:28:11.116
Phoebe.

392
00:28:11.356 --> 00:28:13.521
Please. please. Don't. Don't.

393
00:28:15.606 --> 00:28:18.413
Hey. What's the matter? You can talk to me.

394
00:28:20.418 --> 00:28:22.663
We like each other. Phoebe. You don't have to be afraid of that.

395
00:28:23.465 --> 00:28:24.427
I'm not gonna hurt you.

396
00:28:26.592 --> 00:28:28.356
Really?

397
00:28:28.437 --> 00:28:32.767
Really. Come here.

398
00:28:41.347 --> 00:28:43.592
Oh. no. Not again.

399
00:28:43.753 --> 00:28:44.474
What?

400
00:28:44.474 --> 00:28:46.639
What do you mean. what? Don't think I don't

401
00:28:46.639 --> 00:28:47.682
know.

402
00:28:52.814 --> 00:28:53.295
Hi.

403
00:28:53.856 --> 00:28:54.418
Hi.

404
00:28:54.498 --> 00:28:56.102
Excuse us. You got a minute?

405
00:29:00.592 --> 00:29:02.918
What is the matter with you? Weren't you supposed to be--

406
00:29:02.998 --> 00:29:05.885
ok. but you don't have to yell at me. because I can sense how mad you are.

407
00:29:05.885 --> 00:29:08.370
Ok. just because you can sense doesn't mean I can't vent.

408
00:29:08.370 --> 00:29:09.493
Where are we going right now?

409
00:29:09.493 --> 00:29:10.536
To find Piper. I hope.

410
00:29:10.536 --> 00:29:11.337
You know where she is?

411
00:29:11.498 --> 00:29:12.941
Yeah. A little doggie told me.

412
00:29:43.092 --> 00:29:44.375
Come on. Get up.

413
00:30:38.262 --> 00:30:39.705
Ooh! Way to go. Piper.

414
00:30:40.106 --> 00:30:41.229
What? She's good.

415
00:30:51.894 --> 00:30:53.097
I'll take care of them.

416
00:30:54.781 --> 00:30:56.385
Reversal spell! Reversal spell!

417
00:30:56.465 --> 00:30:57.587
All right. uh.

418
00:30:57.668 --> 00:30:58.790
Spell was cast.

419
00:30:58.790 --> 00:30:59.672
Now make it pass.

420
00:30:59.752 --> 00:31:00.314
Remove it now.

421
00:31:00.314 --> 00:31:01.276
Don't ask me how.

422
00:31:06.488 --> 00:31:08.653
Well. it serves you right. What kind of spell was that?

423
00:31:09.696 --> 00:31:12.663
Ok. Piper. I know why you would rather be one of them.

424
00:31:13.545 --> 00:31:16.351
It's because you don't want to feel pain. But you have to feel the pain.

425
00:31:16.512 --> 00:31:20.281
because if you can't feel the pain. then you can't feel the good stuff either. you know?

426
00:31:23.087 --> 00:31:24.130
Right?

427
00:31:32.870 --> 00:31:34.795
Oh. and that was so much better.

428
00:31:37.762 --> 00:31:39.606
Oh. well. uh. you-- it...

429
00:31:47.465 --> 00:31:48.667
Police! Drop your weapons!

430
00:31:52.517 --> 00:31:53.238
Piper.

431
00:32:15.851 --> 00:32:17.535
Now do you believe me?

432
00:32:19.139 --> 00:32:20.502
Go. Get in.

433
00:32:30.927 --> 00:32:32.290
Piper. let's go.

434
00:32:33.733 --> 00:32:34.856
Piper. don't go.

435
00:32:37.342 --> 00:32:38.304
Hurry.

436
00:32:39.908 --> 00:32:40.790
Please.

437
00:33:00.170 --> 00:33:03.770
There's got to be a way to get Piper out of there. I know it.

438
00:33:04.810 --> 00:33:08.010
Unfortunately. the reversal spell. as you so kindly pointed out.

439
00:33:08.090 --> 00:33:10.171
didn't exactly help Piper remember who she was.

440
00:33:10.571 --> 00:33:11.691
What do the Elders think?

441
00:33:12.411 --> 00:33:14.811
They think it had to be a Demon who stuck Leo in Valhalla.

442
00:33:15.051 --> 00:33:16.251
But they're not sure.

443
00:33:16.491 --> 00:33:18.811
Still. it's their leading theory.

444
00:33:18.891 --> 00:33:20.251
Guys. this is about Piper.

445
00:33:20.651 --> 00:33:24.812
Actually. the Elders believe your new power is key to helping save Piper.

446
00:33:24.892 --> 00:33:28.572
My new power? How do they figure? All it's done is make things worse.

447
00:33:28.892 --> 00:33:30.652
There's a reason you received it. and they

448
00:33:30.652 --> 00:33:33.532
-- we believe it's to help save Piper.

449
00:33:33.532 --> 00:33:36.092
So what exactly did you feel the last time from her?

450
00:33:36.092 --> 00:33:38.572
Ah. not much.

451
00:33:38.892 --> 00:33:42.573
And yet you said you felt something familiar -- little things.

452
00:33:42.653 --> 00:33:45.853
Well. I mean. obviously I felt pain...

453
00:33:47.613 --> 00:33:50.253
...and desire...to help.

454
00:33:50.333 --> 00:33:53.373
Ok. well. she helped Darryl. and that wasn't with her Valkyrie powers.

455
00:33:53.453 --> 00:33:54.573
That was with her Charmed powers.

456
00:33:54.573 --> 00:33:56.014
The witch within must still be alive.

457
00:33:56.014 --> 00:33:58.334
And that's how you're gonna reach her.

458
00:33:58.414 --> 00:34:01.774
But how? I mean. just because I could feel some glimmer of Piper's

459
00:34:01.774 --> 00:34:04.334
feelings doesn't mean she can. She's completely cut off from them.

460
00:34:04.574 --> 00:34:05.454
Wait. Wait. Wait. Hold it.

461
00:34:05.694 --> 00:34:07.774
Isn't there a spell in the book that allows somebody to feel what you feel?

462
00:34:07.774 --> 00:34:16.095
Which. in this case would be Piper feeling what you're feeling Piper should be did that make sense?

463
00:34:16.255 --> 00:34:23.215
Um. frighteningly. it did. What about that spell I used on Cole last year.

464
00:34:23.215 --> 00:34:25.375
the one to make him sense whether or not you loved him?

465
00:34:25.535 --> 00:34:27.615
I could reword it for Piper.

466
00:34:28.336 --> 00:34:29.856
Actually. that's worth a shot.

467
00:34:30.256 --> 00:34:32.416
The problem is. you still have to get close to her to try it.

468
00:34:32.496 --> 00:34:33.936
and that's not gonna be easy.

469
00:34:34.016 --> 00:34:35.456
Yeah. especially with Piper's powers.

470
00:34:35.616 --> 00:34:36.656
Maybe I could orb you--

471
00:34:36.656 --> 00:34:40.256
No. Leo. you're the reason she's in this emotional cocoon.

472
00:34:40.336 --> 00:34:43.617
You need to stay far away from her. No offense.

473
00:34:44.257 --> 00:34:48.817
Then the question is. how do we get close enough to her without her kicking our butts?

474
00:34:51.137 --> 00:34:54.097
I could use my new power to counteract hers.

475
00:34:54.577 --> 00:34:55.377
How do you figure?

476
00:34:55.457 --> 00:34:57.457
Well. our powers are emotion- based. right?

477
00:34:58.017 --> 00:35:04.178
If I can channel Piper's feelings. why can't I channel her powers and then use them against her?

478
00:35:22.419 --> 00:35:23.779
What are you doing here?

479
00:35:23.939 --> 00:35:25.139
We're here to take you home.

480
00:35:33.460 --> 00:35:35.540
Why does she always pick on me first?

481
00:35:53.941 --> 00:35:54.981
Paige. now.

482
00:35:55.861 --> 00:35:57.461
Open Piper's heart to reveal

483
00:35:57.461 --> 00:35:59.381
that part which only Phoebe feels.

484
00:35:59.381 --> 00:36:01.141
Send it back from whence it came.

485
00:36:01.221 --> 00:36:02.821
but don't protect her from the pain.

486
00:36:17.142 --> 00:36:17.702
Wait.

487
00:36:17.702 --> 00:36:19.062
Did they harm you?

488
00:36:21.063 --> 00:36:23.703
No. They helped me.

489
00:36:30.663 --> 00:36:32.343
I know what you do here.

490
00:36:32.743 --> 00:36:36.824
I understand its purpose. so you can trust that your secret is safe.

491
00:36:38.824 --> 00:36:40.904
But I think it's time for me to go home.

492
00:37:19.626 --> 00:37:20.346
Jason Dean.

493
00:37:20.666 --> 00:37:21.146
Hi.

494
00:37:21.466 --> 00:37:24.747
Hi. Phoebe. I was starting to get a little worried.

495
00:37:24.747 --> 00:37:26.347
Did you get all my messages?

496
00:37:26.507 --> 00:37:29.307
Yeah. I did. And I'm sorry I didn't call you back. but -

497
00:37:29.547 --> 00:37:30.667
Let me guess. Something came up.

498
00:37:31.067 --> 00:37:33.547
You are a mysterious woman. Phoebe.

499
00:37:33.787 --> 00:37:34.587
Is that a bad thing?

500
00:37:34.747 --> 00:37:38.187
No. It's a good thing. except for when I'm trying to figure you out.

501
00:37:38.507 --> 00:37:40.348
Well. if it makes you feel any better.

502
00:37:40.428 --> 00:37:42.988
I'm having a hard time figuring myself out these days.

503
00:37:42.988 --> 00:37:48.028
I'm glad. I mean. I'm. you know. not that you're having trouble.

504
00:37:48.188 --> 00:37:52.748
It's just that it's not about me. It's not about me. is it?

505
00:37:52.828 --> 00:37:57.709
No. It's not about you. It's just that. uh

506
00:37:58.109 --> 00:38:01.469
...my feelings have been a little mixed up lately.

507
00:38:01.869 --> 00:38:03.949
Well. long- distance relationships are not easy.

508
00:38:04.349 --> 00:38:06.349
No. they're not.

509
00:38:07.869 --> 00:38:11.630
So. am-- am-- am I gonna see you again before I leave?

510
00:38:12.350 --> 00:38:16.830
Uh. I want to. I really do. but I'm not so sure that's a good idea.

511
00:38:17.550 --> 00:38:21.230
I understand. No. that's a lie. I don't.

512
00:38:21.230 --> 00:38:28.751
It's just that my favorite advice columnist once wrote that it's important for guys to be more understanding.

513
00:38:29.551 --> 00:38:31.311
So how am I doing?

514
00:38:31.471 --> 00:38:34.351
Doing great. really great.

515
00:38:37.391 --> 00:38:38.831
So should I call you?

516
00:38:38.831 --> 00:38:44.512
Yeah. You better call me. Have a safe flight.

517
00:38:46.112 --> 00:38:46.672
Thanks.

518
00:38:48.912 --> 00:38:49.392
Bye.

519
00:38:50.112 --> 00:38:50.832
Bye.

520
00:39:09.393 --> 00:39:11.233
Hey. Chris. what are you doing?

521
00:39:11.713 --> 00:39:13.313
Wow. You look amazing.

522
00:39:13.393 --> 00:39:16.194
Thank you. Um. Leave it. I'll help you clean it up tomorrow.

523
00:39:16.354 --> 00:39:18.754
It's ok. I don't mind. It's the least I can do.

524
00:39:18.994 --> 00:39:20.354
What do you mean. the least you can do?

525
00:39:20.434 --> 00:39:23.074
Oh. you know. for fighting with Leo.

526
00:39:23.154 --> 00:39:24.674
Oh. he attacked you. Don't worry about it

527
00:39:25.074 --> 00:39:28.194
Yeah. I know. Like I said. it's cool.

528
00:39:29.634 --> 00:39:30.195
Hi.

529
00:39:30.435 --> 00:39:34.035
Hey. Guess it didn't go that well with Jason.

530
00:39:34.035 --> 00:39:36.355
Well. I went all the way down there to talk to him.

531
00:39:36.515 --> 00:39:40.355
and then I figured maybe it wasn't such a good idea that I even see him.

532
00:39:40.995 --> 00:39:43.395
at least not until I can control my new power.

533
00:39:43.555 --> 00:39:46.916
Judging by how it's been going. it might be just a little bit.

534
00:39:47.076 --> 00:39:48.756
I know. but what am I supposed to do?

535
00:39:48.996 --> 00:39:51.076
I'm gonna have to figure out how to use it sooner or later.

536
00:39:51.396 --> 00:39:54.596
And until then. I'm just gonna stay away from horny men.

537
00:39:55.636 --> 00:39:56.596
Huh. Good luck.

538
00:39:57.156 --> 00:39:58.756
At least your new power helped save Piper.

539
00:39:58.996 --> 00:40:00.196
That's got to be a good thing. right?

540
00:40:00.436 --> 00:40:02.917
Yeah. It won't help her with what she's going through. though.

541
00:40:02.997 --> 00:40:06.917
But at least she's going through it now. And that is a good thing.

542
00:40:06.917 --> 00:40:10.757
Well. let's hope. Well. I'm off to see Oscar.

543
00:40:11.957 --> 00:40:15.237
Whoa. Wait. Oscar the dog?

544
00:40:15.477 --> 00:40:18.678
Yeah. He's having a bit of a tough time adjusting.

545
00:40:18.678 --> 00:40:21.078
I don't really want him roaming the streets by himself.

546
00:40:21.158 --> 00:40:23.158
especially since I'm the one who rescued him.

547
00:40:24.038 --> 00:40:26.758
You know. I was having trouble with the whole idea of that temp agency thing.

548
00:40:26.838 --> 00:40:29.958
But I'm kind of digging it now. It's all right.

549
00:40:30.118 --> 00:40:31.238
Wait. wait. About Oscar--

550
00:40:31.398 --> 00:40:32.118
Bye.

551
00:40:41.319 --> 00:40:42.199
Who is it?

552
00:40:42.519 --> 00:40:43.399
It's me.

553
00:40:44.839 --> 00:40:45.399
Come in.

554
00:40:50.760 --> 00:40:51.160
Hi.

555
00:40:52.040 --> 00:40:52.920
Hi.

556
00:40:56.120 --> 00:40:57.160
Want to hold him?

557
00:40:58.920 --> 00:41:00.280
Are you kidding?

558
00:41:10.201 --> 00:41:11.961
Oh. he's gotten so big.

559
00:41:12.601 --> 00:41:13.241
Yeah.

560
00:41:21.081 --> 00:41:23.002
Look out. Whoa. Yeah.

561
00:41:25.882 --> 00:41:32.362
Look. Piper. I...want to say I'm sorry for taking away your feelings.

562
00:41:32.362 --> 00:41:37.162
Leo. you don't have to apologize. I know that you were just trying to help me.

563
00:41:37.162 --> 00:41:41.803
I do. And it wasn't your fault you weren't around to take the spell away.

564
00:41:42.203 --> 00:41:46.043
Well. it's somebody's fault. And I want to find out whose.

565
00:41:47.723 --> 00:41:55.164
The other Elders want me to stick around until I do to make sure nobody's targeting us again.

566
00:41:55.244 --> 00:41:57.244
So you're still an Elder. then.

567
00:41:57.484 --> 00:41:59.244
Yeah.

568
00:42:02.284 --> 00:42:05.084
Um. I need to ask you a favor.

569
00:42:05.644 --> 00:42:06.844
Anything.

570
00:42:08.364 --> 00:42:14.765
I need some space from you. I mean. who knows?

571
00:42:14.925 --> 00:42:19.085
This might actually turn out to be a good thing for me in the long run.

572
00:42:19.565 --> 00:42:25.646
I might be able to live some semblance of a normal life. not being married to an angel.

573
00:42:29.886 --> 00:42:38.046
I get why you have to leave. Leo. And I understand that you can't ignore your calling.

574
00:42:39.726 --> 00:42:41.727
But I do have to deal with it somehow

575
00:42:42.607 --> 00:42:46.687
-- with being alone...with being a single mother...

576
00:42:48.127 --> 00:42:51.007
and I can't really do that with you hanging around the house.

577
00:42:55.487 --> 00:42:57.088
I'm sorry.

578
00:43:02.288 --> 00:43:05.968
Leo. please...I need this.

579
00:43:20.369 --> 00:43:21.649
I won't be far.

580
00:43:36.690 --> 00:43:43.490
You deserve a normal life. Piper. I really hope you find it.

581
00:43:44.305 --> 00:44:44.818
